# Varuna360 Core — public mirror .gitignore
#
# IMPORTANT: This file is template-owned. It must never be copied from the
# private repo, whose .gitignore enumerates internal-only directories whose
# names should not appear in the public history. Keep this file MINIMAL.

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so

# Virtual environments
venv/
.venv/
env/
ENV/

# Build artifacts
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
*.AppImage

# User-local settings and data
app_settings.json
settings.json
*.chtk
*.log

# User profiles and chart storage — auto-generated by the app on first
# launch. Kept local; never synced or committed. Mirrors the RSYNC_EXCLUDES
# and GATE_3_SKIP_DIR_PREFIXES rules in release_gates/ so that pre-flight
# checks don't false-positive on clean mirror clones after a test launch.
profiles/
chtk_files/

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~
.vscode/
.idea/

# AI assistant config and knowledge files — defense layer 3 of 4.
# These should never reach the public mirror because the upstream release
# pipeline (release_gates/check_static.py Gate 1 + sync_to_mirror.py
# RSYNC_EXCLUDES) blocks them at the source. This .gitignore entry is the
# last line of defense: if anything ever slips through the upstream gates
# and lands in the mirror working tree, `git add -A` in the mirror will
# still skip it. A genuine open-source contributor cloning the repo will
# also have their local AI tooling files ignored automatically.
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
GOALS.md
AI_CONTEXT.md
INSTRUCTIONS.md
.claude
.claude/
.agents/
.cursorrules
.aider*
.windsurfrules
